punitive figure.

807
00:51:33,567 --> 00:51:36,445
Guess what he suggested? $30!

808
00:51:40,407 --> 00:51:42,762
Does that make any sense? $30.

809
00:51:42,847 --> 00:51:45,486
That's 30 mina. That was
the currency of the day, a mina.

810
00:51:45,567 --> 00:51:46,716
Well, minae.

811
00:51:47,327 --> 00:51:48,760
That's plural. Minae.

812
00:51:50,047 --> 00:51:51,002
$30!

813
00:51:51,927 --> 00:51:53,565
Thirty pieces of silver.

814
00:51:54,327 --> 00:51:58,115
And the judges are so pissed that
more of them voted to kill him...

815
00:51:58,207 --> 00:52:00,004
than had voted him guilty
in the first place.

816
00:52:00,087 --> 00:52:01,884
That doesn't make any sense.

817
00:52:02,847 --> 00:52:04,439
Thirty pieces of silver.

818
00:52:05,127 --> 00:52:06,640
Just like the Judas guy.

819
00:52:06,727 --> 00:52:08,126
The Jesus-kisser...

820
00:52:08,767 --> 00:52:10,644
who was also a prissy dresser.

821
00:52:51,887 --> 00:52:55,197
Without a successful completion
of an alcohol treatment program...

822
00:52:55,287 --> 00:52:56,925
you can forget visitation.

823
00:52:57,527 --> 00:52:59,802
You'll be lucky
to get a Christmas card.

824
00:53:00,047 --> 00:53:02,436
That's if there
even is a custody hearing.

825
00:53:04,247 --> 00:53:05,316
What does that mean?

826
00:53:05,407 --> 00:53:07,762
If your wife
convinces a Spanish court...

827
00:53:07,927 --> 00:53:11,158
that you're a danger to the child,
you'll never see him again.

828
00:53:12,287 --> 00:53:15,040
He just has to come home.
He's got to come back.

829
00:53:15,127 --> 00:53:17,277
Pete, can we
have another round here?

830
00:53:19,207 --> 00:53:20,276
I'm fine.

831
00:53:25,087 --> 00:53:26,520
I'll just have to go get him then.

832
00:53:26,607 --> 00:53:29,838
Europe's not Mexico, David.
They've got real borders over there.

833
00:53:29,967 --> 00:53:33,403
You might be able to get in,
but getting out with a 6-year-old?

834
00:53:34,367 --> 00:53:36,835
That's a whole different
kettle of crawdads.

835
00:53:37,407 --> 00:53:39,125
You want to see Jamie again?

836
00:53:39,207 --> 00:53:41,596
- Then you get your life together.
- I'm fine.

837
00:53:42,567 --> 00:53:43,602
Pronto.

838
00:53:53,127 --> 00:53:54,560
Who wants to start?

839
00:54:04,127 --> 00:54:06,595
Hi, my name is David...

840
00:54:07,807 --> 00:54:09,126
and I am an alcoholic.

841
00:54:09,207 --> 00:54:12,085
AA GROUP Hi, David.

842
00:54:17,407 --> 00:54:19,602
So, Mr. Gale...

843
00:54:20,927 --> 00:54:23,487
tell me three personal qualities...

844
00:54:23,567 --> 00:54:25,398
