has been rescheduled.

854
00:55:32,967 --> 00:55:34,719
Her execution date
is set for the eighth.

855
00:55:34,807 --> 00:55:36,763
I have a call
with Washington tonight.

856
00:55:36,847 --> 00:55:39,077
If the national director
commits to emergency funds...

857
00:55:39,167 --> 00:55:41,237
She gets commuted
and you prove the system works.

858
00:55:41,327 --> 00:55:42,806
But I'll save a life.

859
00:55:43,527 --> 00:55:45,279
Where did you get that bruise?

860
00:55:45,607 --> 00:55:47,325
Just doing chores.

861
00:55:47,647 --> 00:55:49,877
Is your cowboy
getting rough with you?

862
00:55:53,967 --> 00:55:55,082
There he is.

863
00:55:55,327 --> 00:55:58,558
Dusty, does she ever invite you over
and not put you to work?

864
00:56:02,447 --> 00:56:04,483
All right, tell me her story.

865
00:56:04,607 --> 00:56:06,563
She was sentenced at 17.

866
00:56:06,767 --> 00:56:09,600
I really want to get behind
this one. She's so articulate.

867
00:56:09,687 --> 00:56:10,722
Who did she kill?

868
00:56:10,807 --> 00:56:12,320
She'll put a face
on the death penalty.

869
00:56:12,527 --> 00:56:14,722
Constance, who did she kill?

870
00:56:15,527 --> 00:56:16,482
A cop.

871
00:56:17,167 --> 00:56:18,236
You're crazy.

872
00:56:18,327 --> 00:56:21,399
Not just your medium-range,
thinks-she's- Roosevelt's- bathrobe...

873
00:56:21,487 --> 00:56:25,321
but I mean stark-raving,
screws-loose, in-the-belfry insane!

874
00:56:25,407 --> 00:56:26,886
Seventeen.

875
00:56:27,447 --> 00:56:29,802
Four years before she could
legally drink a beer.

876
00:56:29,887 --> 00:56:31,764
But she killed a cop, Constance.

877
00:56:31,847 --> 00:56:33,758
Will you help?
Of course.

878
00:56:35,527 --> 00:56:36,880
You're burning up.

879
00:56:48,807 --> 00:56:49,683
Hi, Mr. Gale.

880
00:56:49,767 --> 00:56:51,678
How are you? It's good to see...

881
00:57:03,847 --> 00:57:05,758
Caffeine jolt. We deliver.

882
00:57:05,847 --> 00:57:07,485
Howdy, David.
Howdy, folks.

883
00:57:07,567 --> 00:57:10,365
Hello. My, this is service.
Thank you.

884
00:57:10,447 --> 00:57:12,642
Gladly. Latte on the left there
for you, John.

885
00:57:12,727 --> 00:57:14,080
Mocha.
Thanks.

886
00:57:15,047 --> 00:57:19,006
- She's on the phone to Washington.
- Sinclair, new National Director.

887
00:57:21,967 --> 00:57:24,527
I'm sure we can get some
pulpit time, maybe some cable.

888
00:57:24,607 --> 00:57:26,404
DIRECTOR
Good. I need to go.

889
00:57:26,487 --> 00:57:30,082
I agree the first press release
should focus on the woman's youth.

890
00:57:30,207 --> 00:57:32,437
I'll have Washington
look into counsel competency.

891
00:57:32,527 --> 00:57:35,360
Though I'm almost sure
she's exhausted this on appeal.

892
00:57:35,447 --> 00:57:37,677
- See what resources...
- David's going to go.

893
00:57:37,767 --> 00:57:40,156
I almost forgot.
Gale's not around, is he?

894
00:57:41,247 --> 00:57:43,636
- No.
- Good. Keep it that way.

895
00:57:43,727 --> 00:57:46,161
His relationship
with DeathWatch is over.

896
00:57:46,247 --> 00:57:49,159
Last thing we need is this
rape thing coming back to bite us.

897
00:57:49,247 --> 00:57:51,283
These guys don't stay
on the wagon for long.

898
00:57:51,887 --> 00:57:53,286
I'm serious, Constance.

899
00:57:53,367 --> 00:57:56,279
Ban him from the premises.
I realise the two of you...

900
00:58:03,407 --> 00:58:04,442
David!

901
00:58:20,807 --> 00:58:23,958
Sharon, pick up the phone.
I'm begging you.

902
00:58:24,647 --> 00:58:26,285
He's my son, all right?

903
00:58:26,367 --> 00:58:28,676
He's my son, too,
and I want to talk to him.

904
00:58:28,767 --> 00:58:30,519
You've not let... Hello?

905
00:58:30,887 --> 00:58:33,037
Jamie, is that you?

906
00:58:33,127 --> 00:58:35,641
Hey, little moose horn.

907
00:58:36,407 --> 00:58:38,238
I miss you so much. It's Daddy.

908
00:58:41,127 --> 00:58:44,199
Jamie, wait.
Don't hang up the phone!

909
00:58:45,727 --> 00:58:46,796
God damn it!

910
00:58:56,047 --> 00:58:57,275
Oh, fuck!

911
00:59:45,767 --> 00:59:46,995
You scared me.

912
00:59:47,487 --> 00:59:49,125
My sheep needs a manager.

913
00:59:50,007 --> 00:59:51,042
A manger.

914
00:59:51,207 --> 00:59:52,925
My sheep needs a manger.

915
00:59:54,287 --> 00:59:55,720
Are you okay?

916
00:59:58,287 --> 01:00:00,517
I fell off the wagon
and I hurt myself.

917
01:00:02,447 --> 01:00:03,926
Come on inside.

918
01:00:09,567 --> 01:00:12,798
Do you know why St. Jude
is the patron saint of lost causes?

919
01:00:13,367 --> 01:00:15,278
'Cause his real name was Judas.

920
01:00:16,247 --> 01:00:18,681
Judas! There were two Judases.

921
01:00:19,207 --> 01:00:22,882
Judae, who was the saint guy,
and then the other one...

922
01:00:23,567 --> 01:00:25,444
Judas, who was the bad one.

923
01:00:25,607 --> 01:00:28,679
He's the one who ratted out Jesus
and tried to kiss him.

924
01:00:29,287 --> 01:00:32,085
In medieval times, they would never
pray to the good Judas...

925
01:00:32,167 --> 01:00:35,204
for fear of getting the bad Judas
on the line just by mistake.

926
01:00:35,287 --> 01:00:37,960
Ergo, they never really
gave him business...

927
01:00:38,047 --> 01:00:39,844
unless absolutely desperate.

928
01:00:41,127 --> 01:00:44,244
That's why.
And then they changed his name.

929
01:00:44,887 --> 01:00:46,605
Your mail is blowing.

930
01:00:58,807 --> 01:00:59,762
Oh, shit.

931
01:01:05,167 --> 01:01:08,045
Are you the doctor?
What's wrong with her?

932
01:01:08,127 --> 01:01:09,003
She'll be fine.

933
01:01:09,087 --> 01:01:11,043
- How do you know?
- Calm down.

934
01:01:11,127 --> 01:01:14,517
She was opening her mail and fell
over. I don't know what's wrong.

935
01:01:14,607 --> 01:01:17,485
Please. Is there a doctor?
Wait here.

936
01:01:17,567 --> 01:01:19,842
I have to go with her!
Hold up, Professor!

937
01:01:19,927 --> 01:01:21,804
You want to get arrested again?

938
01:01:24,167 --> 01:01:25,805
How do you know who I am?

939
01:01:25,887 --> 01:01:28,003
I watch the news. Now go wait.

940
01:02:02,887 --> 01:02:05,162
How're we doing?
Fine. How's Constance?

941
01:02:05,287 --> 01:02:06,242
Sleeping.

942
01:02:07,487 --> 01:02:09,125
A leukaemia patient's
condition is...

943
01:02:09,207 --> 01:02:10,720
very susceptible
to external stress...

944
01:02:10,807 --> 01:02:11,683
What?

945
01:02:13,447 --> 01:02:16,598
